</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>InfosetValue</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>InfosetValue</refname>
<refpurpose>
Returns the value of reaching an information set
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
InfosetValue[profile->BEHAV, infoset->INFOSET*] =: NUMBER 
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<function>InfosetValue</function>
returns the value to the controlling player of reaching 
<parameter>infoset</parameter>
when all players follow <parameter>profile</parameter>.
It is an error if
<parameter>profile</parameter> and <parameter>infoset</parameter>
are not defined on the same
extensive form game.
</para>
</refsect1>

